checkSingleValue

public void checkSingleValue(ExportParser _exportParser,
                             String _kind,
                             String _tag,
                             String _value)
Checks for given _tag in the _exportParser if the _value exists and is correct defined. If _value is null, it is checked that no value is defined. The original method is overwritten because for policies another path exists for the values.

Overrides:
checkSingleValue in class AbstractData<PolicyData>
Parameters:
_exportParser - parsed export
_kind - kind of the check
_tag - tag to check
_value - value to check (or null if value is not defined)
